/ ABOUT / 
PantryPal Login and Create Account System
This project is a simple web application that provides 
a login and account creation system. It is built using Node.js, Express, 
and HTML/CSS/JavaScript for the frontend. The application allows users 
to log in or create an account with a user-friendly interface.

/ FEATURES /

Login Page:
-Users can log in using their email or phone number and password.
-Displays error messages for invalid credentials.

Create Account Page:
-Users can create a new account by providing their full name, email, username, and password.
-Includes a checkbox for agreeing to terms and privacy.

Responsive Design:
-Both pages are styled to look clean and professional.
-Fully responsive for different screen sizes.

/ TECHNOLOGIES USED /

backend:
-Node.js
-Express.js
-bcrypt (for password hashing)

Fronted:
-HTML
-CSS
-JavaScript

Other Tools:
-Body-parser (for parsing JSON requests)

/ SETUP IMSTRUCTIONS /
1. Clone the Repository:

git clone <repository-url>
cd 371project

2. Install Dependencies
Run the following command to install 
the required Node.js modules:

npm install

The server will start.


/ PROJECT STRUCTURE /

371project/
│
├── public/
│   ├── index.html          # Login page
│   ├── create-account.html # Create account page
│   ├── styles.css          # CSS for styling
│   ├── app.js              # Frontend JavaScript
│
├── server.js               # Backend server code
├── package.json            # Node.js dependencies
├── package-lock.json       # Dependency lock file
└── README.md               # Project documentation

/ HOW TO USE /

Login Page:
1.Open http://localhost:3000 in your browser.
2.Enter your email or phone number and password.
3.Click Sign In to log in.

Create Account Page
1.Click the Create Account button on the login page.
2.Fill in the form with your details.
3.Click Sign Up to create a new account.

/ ENDPOINTS /

POST /login:
-Validates user credentials and returns a success or error message.

POST /create-account:
-Creates a new user account and stores the hashed password.

/ FEATURE ENHANCEMENTS /

-Add a database (e.g., MongoDB) to store user data persistently.
-Implement password recovery functionality.
-Add email verification for account creation.

